# Documentation sync

When code, data, or user-visible behavior changes, update project docs **as needed** — do not leave README, AGENTS.md, or rules stale.

## Where each doc lives

| File                  | Update when                                                                                   |
| --------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `README.md`           | Human-facing overview changes (site features, i18n URLs, project structure, getting started)  |
| `AGENTS.md`           | Agent-facing stack, commands, layout paths, or conventions change                             |
| `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` | Persistent policies or constraints change (e.g. responsive targets → `responsive-design.mdc`) |

Do not copy the same long content into multiple files. Pick one source of truth; elsewhere use a short summary + link.

## Common triggers

| Change                                                    | Check                                                            |
| --------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `src/data/` (nav, history, site-tech-stack, social-links) | README Site Features / Project Structure                         |
| i18n or URLs (`src/i18n/routing.ts`, `src/proxy.ts`) | README Internationalization; AGENTS Stack                        |
| `src/messages/` (new/changed keys)                        | `i18n-messages.mdc`; README Internationalization if roles change |
| New/changed sections, header, footer behavior             | README Site Features                                             |
| Dependencies or npm scripts                               | README Tech Stack / Getting Started; AGENTS Stack / Commands     |
| Responsive policy                                         | `responsive-design.mdc` (README keeps summary only)              |
| New standing Agent convention                             | New or existing `.mdc` rule                                      |

## Skip doc updates unless the user asks

- Internal refactors with no behavior or README-relevant change
- Typo or formatting-only edits in code
- User explicitly says not to touch documentation

## Workflow

1. After implementing a change, decide what became outdated (human docs / agent docs / rules).
2. Update only the files that need it, with minimal diffs.
3. Ensure README and AGENTS.md do not contradict each other (locale URLs, section descriptions, paths).
